# Excalidraw — Cursor Rules (legacy format)

This file consolidates project rules for Cursor. The canonical source is `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`.

## Memory Bank

Read `docs/memory/activeContext.md` before substantive changes, then consult task-relevant files in `docs/memory/`, `docs/product/`, and `docs/technical/`.

## Protected Files

NEVER modify without explicit approval:

- `packages/excalidraw/scene/renderer.ts` — render pipeline
- `packages/excalidraw/data/restore.ts` — file format compat
- `packages/excalidraw/actions/manager.ts` — action system
- `packages/excalidraw/types.ts` — core types

## Architecture

- Custom state via actionManager — NOT Redux/Zustand/MobX
- Canvas 2D rendering — NOT React DOM for drawing; no react-konva, fabric.js, pixi.js
- No new npm packages without explicit approval

## Package Boundaries (low → high)

1. `@excalidraw/common` — no workspace deps
2. `@excalidraw/math` — depends on common only
3. `@excalidraw/element` — depends on common + math
4. `@excalidraw/utils` — no `@excalidraw/*` runtime deps
5. `@excalidraw/excalidraw` — may consume common, math, element

Never reverse the dependency flow without review.

## Code Conventions

- Functional components + hooks only (no class components)
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`; named exports only
- Strict TypeScript — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types; use `import type` for type-only imports
- Files: kebab-case (`element-utils.ts`), components: PascalCase (`LayerUI.tsx`)

## Styling (SCSS)

- Colocated `*.scss` next to `.tsx` (`import "./Foo.scss"`)
- Use `*.module.scss` where build should scope class names; import shared tokens via `@use`
- Prefer theme/CSS variables over hard-coded colors
- Do not introduce CSS-in-JS for editor UI — stay on SCSS

## Testing

- Vitest + jsdom; use `@excalidraw/*` path aliases
- Update snapshots only for intentional changes: `yarn test:update`
- Do not lower coverage thresholds without review
- Colocate tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## Math and Geometry

- Geometry types: `packages/math/src/types.ts` — `GlobalPoint`, `LocalPoint`, `Vector`, `Line`, `Polygon`, etc.
- Import from `@excalidraw/math`; do not duplicate branded types
- `packages/math` stays pure: no React, no element/excalidraw imports

## Security

- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` for user-controlled content without reviewed sanitization
- Validate URLs; reject `javascript:`, unsafe `data:` schemes; use `rel="noopener noreferrer"` on `target="_blank"`
- Validate `.excalidraw` / scene JSON structure; never execute code from data files
- No committed API keys/tokens — use env vars and CI secrets
- No new npm packages without approval; prefer audited, maintained deps
- Treat socket/Firebase messages as untrusted; validate before use

### Data and Restore

- Treat files and JSON in restore/import paths as hostile; validate shapes, types, ranges
- Never `eval`, `new Function`, or dynamic `import()` from saved data
- Preserve backward compat but do not relax validation for malformed data

### excalidraw-app

- Secrets via `import.meta.env` only; keep `.env` files out of git
- Scrub secrets from error reports; avoid caching authenticated responses in SW
- No arbitrary scripts/inline handlers from user-controlled config

## Development Commands

```bash
yarn start            # Vite dev server
yarn build            # Production build
yarn build:packages   # Build common → math → element → excalidraw
yarn test:typecheck   # TypeScript type checking
yarn test:update      # Run tests with snapshot updates
yarn test:all         # typecheck + eslint + prettier + tests
yarn fix              # Auto-fix formatting and linting
```

## Context7 MCP

Use Context7 MCP (`resolve-library-id` → `query-docs`) to fetch current library/framework documentation even for well-known libraries. Training data may be outdated.
